# Source asset dropoffs at the repo root — canonical copies live under
# eval-lab/public/assets/. Keeping the root files out of git prevents
# duplicate-asset confusion and a 600KB+ White.png blob in history.
/White.png
/Comer-industries_placeholder-logo.png

# Raw POV footage — large source videos stay out of git (regenerate the web
# transcode from source with ffmpeg). The small web-optimized POV clip that the
# synthetic-pov page streams (eval-lab/public/assets/phase8_pov.mp4, ~17 MB
# H.264 540x720) IS committed so it deploys to the hosted site.
/Phase_8_Video.MP4
*.MP4
# …but DO ship the small web POV clip (case-insensitive FS makes *.MP4 match it).
!eval-lab/public/assets/phase8_pov.mp4
